              ]
            }
          ],
          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Neutron-proton capture using polarized neutrons from",
                " 19 to 50 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G.Fink",
                "P.Doll",
                "S.Hauber",
                "M.Haupenthal",
                "H.O.Klages",
                "H.Schieler",
                "F.Smend",
                "G.D.Wicke"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2GERKFK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERKFK"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Karlsruhe Cyclotron, providing a",
                " pulsed beam of polarized deuterons, was used. The",
                " polarization of the deuteron beam was 56.2%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLNS",
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Polarized neutrons were produced",
                "            using a liquid deuterium target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The polarized neutron beam showed a continuous spect-",
                " rum with a maximum around 27.5 - 30 MeV. The sign of",
                " the polarization was reversed every 4 sec, and the",
                " difference in the neutron flux for the two spin states",
                " was less than 0.5%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   The neutron energies were determined by the",
                " Time-Of-Flight over the 6.5 m flight path between the",
                " source and the NE213 target. Neutron energy bins of",
                " 3-4 MeV were used."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In-beam gamma-ray spectroscopy."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A coincidence between the deuteron recoil in",
                " the NE213 and the capture gamma-ray was required."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The deuteron recoils were detected in the tar-",
                " get, which was an NE213 liquid scintillator of cylin-",
                " drical shape, viewed at each end by an XP2020 Pm-tube,",
                " cooled to -10 degrees Celsius. The detector had good",
                " energy and time resolution. The singles count rate was",
                " 0.5 MHz. Stability of the pulse-height was achieved",
                " using a pulsed light-emitting diode. The target reso-",
                " lution was about 16% for several MeV recoiling protons"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The capture gamma-rays were detected with three",
                " NaI detectors, placed at angles of 55, 90 and 125 deg-",
                " rees in the laboratory system. The dimensions of the",
                " crystals were 16 x 16 x 24 cm3. The detectors were",
                " actively shielded with plastic scintillators, and had",
                " also heavy passive shields. The detectors were cali-",
                " brated using gamma-rays from reactions on carbon in",
                " the NE213 target. The background from scattered neu-",
                " trons were rejected by Time-Of-Flight techniques. The",
                " detector resolution was about 6% for 15.11 MeV",
                " gamma-rays. Stability of the pulse-height was achieved",
                " using a pulsed light-emitting diode. The total event",
                " rate, with all timing and coincidence requirements,",
                " was typically 100 Hz."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  The neutron beam flux was monitored with a",
                " low-mass multiwire proportional chamber, positioned",
                " in the neutron beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Recoil deuterons."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Capture gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A scintillating target, consisting of 289 cm3 liquid",
                " NE213, was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Corrections were applied for gain instabilities.",
                " Multiple neutron scattering was minimized by hard",
                " constraints on the data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The error is dominated by the one standard",
                " deviation statistical error. The maximum multiple",
                " scattering effect is included as a systematic error."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The cross section at 0 and 180 degrees were estimated",
                " by detailed balance calculations from experimental",
                " forward disintegration cross sections. The data given",
                " were derived by the angular distributions, constrained",
                " at the three measured angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
